just_use dealer.py

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: random-deal initial state generator for self-play

Produces a random LynRummy initial state — board layout +
hand cards — that auto_player consumes when starting a fresh
session. Each call returns a new pseudo-random deal.

The Go server has its own dealer with a fixed seed; relying
on it would converge every self-play game to the same stuck
states. Python's `dealer.deal()` exists so the agent's
self-play actually explores different draws.

## Pointers

- Consumers: `auto_player.py`, several hunt scripts
  (`beginner_hunt.py`, `complex_hunt.py`, etc.).
- Companion: `feedback_random_vs_deterministic` (the deal
  divergence story).
